## 15.2 Biggest Unknown Right Now
What is the single biggest uncertainty in your project at this stage?

**Response:**  
`[The biggest uncertainty initially was the reliability and consistency of flex sensor readings across different hand sizes and grip styles. During testing, this concern proved significant — sensor values fluctuated even when fingers were held still, and thresholds were difficult to standardize.
This led to a key design pivot: replacing flex sensors with a touch-based jumper wire system, which provided more stable and binary input signals. The current uncertainty lies in ensuring that touch inputs remain distinct and do not accidentally trigger due to unintended finger contact.]`

