# 17. Build Documentation

## 17.1 Fabrication Process
Describe how the project was physically made.

Include:
- cutting,
- 3D printing,
- assembly,
- fastening,
- wiring,
- finishing,
- revisions.

**Response:**  
`[We began by testing flex sensors individually using a voltage divider circuit with the ESP32. While initial readings showed variation between bent and straight positions, the values were inconsistent and unstable during repeated use. Even after averaging readings and recalibrating thresholds, the sensors failed to produce reliable gesture classification.
Due to these limitations, we pivoted to a touch-based input system using jumper wires. Conductive wires were placed along the fingers of the glove such that specific finger contacts would complete circuits corresponding to Rock, Paper, and Scissors.
This approach eliminated ambiguity in sensor readings and provided clear binary inputs. The wires were taped along the glove and routed to the ESP32 via jumper connections. The ESP32 and breadboard were kept off-glove to maintain flexibility and reduce strain.
This iteration significantly improved system reliability and responsiveness.]`

